flowchart TB
    N1["1. neo-zkvm-host: Trust boundary shows what must be proven rather than believed."]
    N2["2. Trusted base: verification key, guest program hash, verifier rules"]
    N3["3. Untrusted input: L2 batch | guest ELF | prover configuration"]
    N4["4. Validation boundary: public input, proof envelope, verification key, and public output must match"]
    N5["5. Replay and ordering: proof binds batch range and state root to prevent cross-batch reuse"]
    N6["6. Authority: prover cannot advance state; verifier-accepted output is consumed"]
    N7["7. External systems: proof backend, L1 verifier, NeoFS DA, report consumers"]
    N8["8. Observed evidence: proof id, public output, verification result, duration, and failure reason"]
    N1 --> N2
    N1 --> N3
    N1 --> N4
    N1 --> N5
    N1 --> N6
    N1 --> N7
    N1 --> N8
    N2 -. constrains .-> N4
    N4 -. produces .-> N5
    N5 -. consumed by .-> N6
